                    "value": 3
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The innkeeper gives some pertinent advice to a single creature other than themself. For 24 hours, when that creature fails a skill check or saving throw, they can recall this advice and reroll the check, using the second result instead. Once that creature uses this ability, its effect ends. A creature that receives the Innkeeper's Advice is temporarily immune to the ability for 1 month.</p>"
